Fill and boil your kettle.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat for the pasta.

Add the @penne pasta{180%g} and @salt{0.5%tsp} to the boiling water and bring
back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil
and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Add the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g} into the garlic.

Add the @water for the sauce{150%ml} and stir to combine.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has reduced and thickened
slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @peas{120%g} to the sauce, then add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the penne is cooked, add to the sauce and stir to coat well.

Stir through the @fresh pesto{50%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and mix well.

Share your creamy pesto pasta between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!